The filesystem MCP server has been configured. Here's what was added to `~/.claude/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "filesystem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "C:/Users/matta"]
    }
  }
}
```

**To activate it**, restart Claude Code. After restarting, the filesystem MCP server will have read/write access to `C:\Users\matta` and you'll be able to use it to interact with files in your home directory.
